cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of neural networks, specifically deep belief networks. The paper also mentions image classification and speech recognition, which are common applications of neural networks. 

The cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category is also likely as the paper focuses on hardware implementations of neural networks and explores methods to reduce power consumption. 

The cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category is another possibility as the paper discusses probabilistic generative neural networks and their applications. 

The cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is also possible as the paper mentions occlusion removal, which is a common problem in computer vision. 

Finally, the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper discusses the use of criticality analysis to identify nodes in the network that can operate with limited precision while maintaining accuracy levels, which could be considered a control problem.
